import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['rate'] = pd.to_numeric(data['rate'], errors='coerce')
    sns.boxplot(x='state', y='rate', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of rate across different states?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['rate'] = pd.to_numeric(data['rate'], errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['rate'])
    data = data.groupby(['region'])['rate'].mean().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='region', y='rate', data=data)
    chart.set_title('What is the average rate in each region?')
    chart.axhline(data['rate'].mean(), color='red', label='Average rate')
    chart.legend()
    return chart

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['state'])
    data = data.sort_values(by='state')
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.barplot(x="state", y="rate", data=data, palette="Blues_d")
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90, ha="right")
    plt.title('How does the rate vary across different states?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['rate'] = pd.to_numeric(data['rate'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='rate', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['rate'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['rate'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of rate?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
